@mmahacek @indigo423 I've added the BSM example. Two questions here:

1. Do we want to start to have example code somewhere else? Similar to the references? I think we always wanted to separate this, no? 
2. Isn't the `vbname` always an event parameter? If so, I am wondering if we should call like this in these descriptions: https://github.com/OpenNMS/opennms/pull/6955/files#diff-c8d6cc2c1f5ad9d047ace92b42d00f237d91c67e60bf1aa7b49cfed21f144fc2R124 Or can a varbind also something else than an event parameter?

```js
  var ret = this.n === 0 ? _reduced(result) : this.xf['@@transducer/step'](result, input);
  return this.n >= 0 && this.i >= this.n ? _reduced(ret) : ret;
```

Though there's no problem to do `_reduced(_reduced(result)`, there's also no need to wrap `result` early.

`_reduced` will only wrap the real value once:

```js
export default function _reduced(x) {
  return x && x['@@transducer/reduced'] ? x :
    {
      '@@transducer/value': x,
      '@@transducer/reduced': true
    };
}
```

I thought it will iterate more than 1 time when `n` is 0, but I'm wrong, it will exit after the first iteration, as follows:

```js
return this.n >= 0 && this.i >= this.n ? _reduced(ret) : ret;
```

`n` equals 0, and `i` is 0 too, so the `ret` will be wrapped with `_reduced` in the first iteration, and exit immediately.

